The paper deals with connectivity-related concepts in graph theory, specifically for directed graphs. This suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-categories. The paper also presents improved algorithms for computing maximal 2-edge- and 2-vertex-connected subgraphs, which involves graph traversal and manipulation, indicating a possible fit for the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-category. The use of time complexity analysis and optimization further suggests a potential fit for the cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) sub-category. Finally, the paper may also belong to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category, as connectivity is a fundamental concept in network analysis.
